96  // UNITS IN INPUT FILES
97  // ... Always use atomic units
98  // ... ... Positions in a0 (bohr)
99  // ... ... Multipole moment of rank k in e(a0)**k
100  // ... ... Dipole polarizability in A³ (Angstrom cubed)
101 
102  // UNITS USED INTERNALLY
103  // ... Use nm instead of a0 and A
104  // ... ... Positions in nm
105  // ... ... Multipole moment of rank k in e(nm)**k
106  // ... ... Dipole polarizability in nm³
107 
108  // CONVERSION FACTORS
109  // ... Electric field (N/C) = Electric field (int)
110  // * 1/4PiEps0(SI) * e * 1e+18
111  // ... Energy (eV) = Energy (int) * 1/4PiEps0(SI) * e * 1e+09
112  //
113  // ... Potential (V) = Potential(int) * 1/4PiEps0(SI) * e * 1e+0.9

300  inline double T21s_20() { return R5 * 0.5 * sqrt(3) * (35*rbz*rbz*ray*raz - 5*ray*raz + 10*rbz*ray*czz + 10*rbz*raz*cyz + 2*cyz*czz); }
301  inline double T22c_20() { return R5 * 0.25 * sqrt(3) * (35*rbz*rbz*rax*rax - 35*rbz*rbz*ray*ray - 5*rax*rax + 5*ray*ray + 20*rbz*rax*cxz - 20*rbz*ray*cyz + 2*cxz*cxz - 2*cyz*cyz); }
302  inline double T22s_20() { return R5 * 0.5 * sqrt(3) * (35*rbz*rbz*rax*ray - 5*rax*ray + 10*rbz*rax*cyz + 10*rbz*ray*cxz + 2*cxz*cyz); }
303  inline double T21s_21c() { return R5 * (35*rbx*rbz*ray*raz + 5*rbx*ray*czz + 5*rbx*raz*cyz + 5*rbz*ray*czx + 5*rbz*raz*cyx + cyx*czz + czx*cyz); }
304  inline double T22c_21c() { return R5 * 0.5 * (35*rbx*rbz*rax*rax - 35*rbx*rbz*ray*ray + 10*rbx*rax*cxz - 10*rbx*ray*cyz + 10*rbz*rax*cxx - 10*rbz*ray*cyx + 2*cxx*cxz - 2*cyx*cyz); }
305  inline double T22s_21c() { return R5 * (35*rbx*rbz*rax*ray + 5*rbx*rax*cyz + 5*rbx*ray*cxz + 5*rbz*rax*cyx + 5*rbz*ray*cxx + cxx*cyz + cyx*cxz); }
306  inline double T22c_21s() { return R5 * 0.5 * (35*rby*rbz*rax*rax - 35*rby*rbz*ray*ray + 10*rby*rax*cxz - 10*rby*ray*cyz + 10*rbz*rax*cxy - 10*rbz*ray*cyy + 2*cxy*cxz - 2*cyy*cyz); }
307  inline double T22s_21s() { return R5 * (35*rby*rbz*rax*ray + 5*rby*rax*cyz + 5*rby*ray*cxz + 5*rbz*rax*cyy + 5*rbz*ray*cxy + cxy*cyz + cyy*cxz); }
308  inline double T22s_22c() { return R5 * 0.5 * (35*rbx*rbx*rax*ray - 35*rby*rby*rax*ray + 10*rbx*rax*cyx + 10*rbx*ray*cxx - 10*rby*rax*cyy - 10*rby*ray*cxy + 2*cxx*cyx - 2*cxy*cyy); }
309 
310  Topology *_top;
311  QMultipole *_em;
312 
313  };

649 void QMultipole::EStatify(Topology *top, Property *options) {
650 
651  cout << endl << "... ... Estatify system: ";
652 
653  string key = "options.qmultipole";
654  string allocFile = options->get(key+".multipoles").as<string> ();
655 
656  // ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
657  // Load polar-site indices from XML //
658  // ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
659 
660  // => Output to maps:
661  map<string, vector<int> > alloc_frag_mpoleIdx;
662  map<string, vector<string> > alloc_frag_mpoleName;
663  map<string, string > alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_n;
664  map<string, string > alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_e;
665  map<string, string > alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_h;
666 
667  Property allocation; // <- Which polar sites are part of which fragment?
668  load_property_from_xml(allocation, allocFile.c_str());
669 
670 
671  /* --- MULTIPOLES.XML Structure ---
672  *
673  * <topology>
674  *
675  * <molecules>
676  * <molecule>
677  * <name></name>
678  *
679  * <segments>
680  *
681  * <segment>
682  * <name>DCV</name>
683  *
684  * <multipoles_n></multipoles_n>
685  * <multipoles_e></multipoles_e>
686  * <multipoles_h></multipoles_h>
687  *
688  * <map2md></map2md>
689  *
690  * <fragments>
691  * <fragment>
692  * <name></name>
693  * <mpoles></mpoles>
694  * </fragment>
695  * </fragments>
696  * ...
697  * ...
698  */
699 
700 
701  key = "topology.molecules.molecule";
702  list<Property *> mols = allocation.Select(key);
703  list<Property *>::iterator molit;
704  for (molit = mols.begin(); molit != mols.end(); molit++) {
705 
706  string molName = (*molit)->get("name").as<string> ();
707 
708  key = "segments.segment";
709  list<Property *> segs = (*molit)->Select(key);
710  list<Property *>::iterator segit;
711 
712  for (segit = segs.begin(); segit != segs.end(); segit++) {
713 
714  string segName = (*segit)->get("name").as<string> ();
715 
716  // GDMA filenames for cation (h), neutral (n), anion (e) state
717  string mpoleFile_n = (*segit)->get("multipoles_n").as<string> ();
718  alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_n[segName] = mpoleFile_n;
719  if ( (*segit)->exists("multipoles_e")) {
720  string mpoleFile_e = (*segit)->get("multipoles_e").as<string>();
721  alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_e[segName] = mpoleFile_e;
722  }
723  if ( (*segit)->exists("multipoles_h")) {
724  string mpoleFile_h = (*segit)->get("multipoles_h").as<string>();
725  alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_h[segName] = mpoleFile_h;
726  }
727 
728  // Default: Project multipoles onto rigidified coordinates
729  if ( (*segit)->exists("map2md")) {
730  int map2md = (*segit)->get("map2md").as<int>();
731  _map2md[segName] = (map2md == 0) ? false : true;
732  }
733  else {
734  _map2md[segName] = false; // i.e. map to rigidified coordinates
735  }
736 
737  key = "fragments.fragment";
738  list<Property *> frags = (*segit)->Select(key);
739  list<Property *>::iterator fragit;
740 
741  for (fragit = frags.begin(); fragit != frags.end(); fragit++) {
742 
743  string fragName = (*fragit)->get("name").as<string> ();
744  string mapKeyName = fragName + segName + molName;
745 
746  string mpoles = (*fragit)->get("mpoles").as<string> ();
747 
748  Tokenizer tokPoles(mpoles, " \t\n");
749  vector<string> mpoleInfo;
750  tokPoles.ToVector(mpoleInfo);
751 
752  vector<int> mpoleIdcs;
753  vector<string> mpoleNames;
754 
755  vector<string> ::iterator strit;
756  for (strit=mpoleInfo.begin(); strit<mpoleInfo.end(); strit++) {
757 
758  Tokenizer tokPoleInfo( (*strit), " :");
759  vector<string> poleInfo;
760  tokPoleInfo.ToVector(poleInfo);
761 
762  int mpoleIdx = boost::lexical_cast<int>(poleInfo[0]);
763  string mpoleName = poleInfo[1];
764 
765  mpoleIdcs.push_back(mpoleIdx);
766  mpoleNames.push_back(mpoleName);
767 
768  }
769 
770  alloc_frag_mpoleIdx[mapKeyName] = mpoleIdcs;
771  alloc_frag_mpoleName[mapKeyName] = mpoleNames;
772  }
773  }
774  }
775 
776  // ++++++++++++++++++++++ //
777  // Parse GDMA punch files //
778  // ++++++++++++++++++++++ //
779 
780  // => Output to APolarSite Container (template container)
781  map<string, vector<APolarSite*> > map_seg_APolarSites;
782  map<string, vector<bool> > map_seg_chrgStates;
783 
784 
785  // Multipoles for neutral state
786  int state = 0;
787  map<string, string > ::iterator strit;
788  for (strit = alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_n.begin();
789  strit != alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_n.end();
790  strit++) {
791 
792  string segName = strit->first;
793  string filename = strit->second;
794 
795  vector< APolarSite* > poles = ParseGdmaFile(filename, state);
796 
797  map_seg_APolarSites[segName] = poles;
798  map_seg_chrgStates[segName].resize(3);
799  map_seg_chrgStates[segName][0] = false; // <- negative
800  map_seg_chrgStates[segName][1] = true; // <- neutral
801  map_seg_chrgStates[segName][2] = false; // <- positive
802  poles.clear();
803 
804  }
805 
806  // Multipoles for negative state
807  state = -1;
808  if ( alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_e.size() ) {
809  for (strit = alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_e.begin();
810  strit != alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_e.end();
811  strit++) {
812  string segName = strit->first;
813  string filename = strit->second;
814 
815  vector< APolarSite* > polesAnion = ParseGdmaFile(filename, state);
816  map_seg_chrgStates[segName][state+1] = true;
817 
818  // Merge with polar sites for neutral state
819  vector< APolarSite* > polesNeutral = map_seg_APolarSites[segName];
820 
821  assert(polesAnion.size() == polesNeutral.size());
822  for (int i = 0; i < polesNeutral.size(); i++) {
823 
824  polesNeutral[i]->setQs( polesAnion[i]->getQs(state), state );
825  polesNeutral[i]->setPs( polesAnion[i]->getPs(state), state );
826  delete polesAnion[i];
827  }
828  polesAnion.clear();
829  }
830  }
831 
832  // Multipoles for positive state
833  state = +1;
834  if ( alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_h.size() ) {
835  for (strit = alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_h.begin();
836  strit != alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_h.end();
837  strit++) {
838  string segName = strit->first;
839  string filename = strit->second;
840 
841  vector< APolarSite* > polesCation = ParseGdmaFile(filename, state);
842  map_seg_chrgStates[segName][state+1] = true;
843 
844  // Merge with polar sites for neutral state
845  vector< APolarSite* > polesNeutral = map_seg_APolarSites[segName];
846 
847  assert(polesCation.size() == polesNeutral.size());
848  for (int i = 0; i < polesNeutral.size(); i++) {
849 
850  polesNeutral[i]->setQs( polesCation[i]->getQs(state), state );
851  polesNeutral[i]->setPs( polesCation[i]->getPs(state), state );
852  delete polesCation[i];
853  }
854  polesCation.clear();
855  }
856  }
857 
858  // +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
859  // Forward information on polar-site templates to topology //
860  // +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
861 
862  // Containers to use for mapping
863  // map<string, vector<APolarSite*> > map_seg_APolarSites;
864  // map<string, vector<int> > alloc_frag_mpoleIdx;
865  // map<string, vector<string> > alloc_frag_mpoleName;
866 
867  // TO CONTINUE FROM HERE ...
868  // Loop over segments, loop over fragments in segments.
869  // => For each segment, look up associated polar sites using map 1;
870  // => For each fragment, look up associated
871  // polar sites idcs. using map 2;
872  // => For each index in retrieved container, create new polar site,
873  // importing information from polar site container of segment
874  // => Translate positions to MD frame, copy local frame from
875  // fragment
876 
877  _map_seg_APolarSites = map_seg_APolarSites;
878  _map_seg_chrgStates = map_seg_chrgStates;
879  _alloc_frag_mpoleIdx = alloc_frag_mpoleIdx;
880  _alloc_frag_mpoleName = alloc_frag_mpoleName;
881 
882 }

903 vector<vec> QMultipole::ParseCubeFileHeader(string filename) {
904 
905  vector< vec > cube;
906  cube.resize(5);
907 
908  // STRUCTURE CUBE CONTAINER
909  // 0 1 2 3 4
910  // | | | | | |
911  // ox oy oz Nx Ny Nz xx xy xz yx yy yz zx zy zz
912 
913  std::string line;
914  int lineCount = 0;
915 
916  double Nx = 0;
917  double Ny = 0;
918  double Nz = 0;
919  double BOHR2NM = 0.0529189379;
920  double ANGSTROM2NM = 0.1;
921  double ext2nm = BOHR2NM;
922 
923  std::ifstream intt;
924  intt.open(filename.c_str());
925 
926  if (intt.is_open()) {
927  while (intt.good()) {
928 
929  ++lineCount;
930 
931  std::getline(intt, line);
932  vector<string> split;
933  Tokenizer toker(line, " ");
934  toker.ToVector(split);
935 
936  // First two lines are comment lines
937  if (lineCount == 1 || lineCount == 2) { continue; }
938 
939 
940 
941  // Skip empty lines
942  if ( split.size() == 0) { continue; }
943 
944  // => Interesting information here
945  if (lineCount == 3) {
946 
947  assert( split.size() == 4 );
948  double ox = boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[1] );
949  double oy = boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[2] );
950  double oz = boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[3] );
951 
952  cube[0] = vec(ox, oy, oz);
953  }
954 
955  /*
956  STRUCTURE SAMPLE CPMD CUBE FILE
957  OUTER LOOP: X, MIDDLE LOOP: Y, INNER LOOP: Z
958  3 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000
959  40 0.283459 0.000000 0.000000
960  40 0.000000 0.283459 0.000000
961  40 0.000000 0.000000 0.283459
962  8 0.000000 5.570575 5.669178 5.593517
963  1 0.000000 5.562867 5.669178 7.428055
964  1 0.000000 7.340606 5.669178 5.111259
965  : : : : : :
966  : : : : : :
967  : : : : : :
968  In this case there will be 40 x 40 x 40 floating point values
969  : : : : : :
970  : : : : : :
971  : : : : : :
972  */
973 
974  if (lineCount == 4) {
975 
976  assert( split.size() == 4 );
977  Nx = boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[0] );
978  ext2nm = (Nx > 0) ? BOHR2NM : ANGSTROM2NM;
979  Nx = (Nx >= 0) ? Nx : -Nx;
980  double xx = ext2nm * boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[1] );
981  double xy = ext2nm * boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[2] );
982  double xz = ext2nm * boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[3] );
983 
984  cube[2] = vec(xx, xy, xz);
985  }
986 
987  if (lineCount == 5) {
988 
989  assert( split.size() == 4 );
990  Ny = boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[0] );
991  ext2nm = (Ny > 0) ? BOHR2NM : ANGSTROM2NM;
992  Ny = (Ny >= 0) ? Ny : -Ny;
993  double yx = ext2nm * boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[1] );
994  double yy = ext2nm * boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[2] );
995  double yz = ext2nm * boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[3] );
996 
997  cube[3] = vec(yx, yy, yz);
998  }
999 
1000  if (lineCount == 6) {
1001 
1002  assert( split.size() == 4 );
1003  Nz = boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[0] );
1004  ext2nm = (Nz > 0) ? BOHR2NM : ANGSTROM2NM;
1005  Nz = (Nz >= 0) ? Nz : -Nz;
1006  double zx = ext2nm * boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[1] );
1007  double zy = ext2nm * boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[2] );
1008  double zz = ext2nm * boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[3] );
1009 
1010  cube[4] = vec(zx, zy, zz);
1011  cube[1] = vec(Nx, Ny, Nz);
1012  }
1013 
1014  // Header at finish?
1015  if (lineCount > 6) {
1016  break;
1017  }
1018  }
1019  }
1020  else { cout << endl << "ERROR: No such file " << filename << endl; }
1021 
1022  // Convert origin
1023  cube[0] *= ext2nm;
1024 
1025  return cube;
1026 }

1168 void QMultipole::CalculateESP(vector< APolarSite* > &poles, FILE *out) {
1169 
1170  // Calculate potential for each voxel, write to output on the fly
1171  Interactor actor = Interactor(NULL, this);
1172  vector< APolarSite* >::iterator pit;
1173 
1174  vec Cxyz = _cube[0];
1175 
1176  vec C0 = _cube[0];
1177  vec Cx = _cube[2];
1178  vec Cy = _cube[3];
1179  vec Cz = _cube[4];
1180 
1181  int Nx = int(_cube[1].getX() + 0.5);
1182  int Ny = int(_cube[1].getY() + 0.5);
1183  int Nz = int(_cube[1].getZ() + 0.5);
1184 
1185 
1186  // Prepare cube file: Header
1187  double NM2BOHR = 1 / 0.0529189379;
1188  fprintf(out, "%5ld %3.7f %3.7f %3.7f \n",
1189  poles.size(),
1190  Cxyz.getX()*NM2BOHR,
1191  Cxyz.getY()*NM2BOHR,
1192  Cxyz.getZ()*NM2BOHR);
1193  fprintf(out, "%5d %3.7f %3.7f %3.7f \n",
1194  Nx,
1195  Cx.getX()*NM2BOHR,
1196  Cx.getY()*NM2BOHR,
1197  Cx.getZ()*NM2BOHR);
1198  fprintf(out, "%5d %3.7f %3.7f %3.7f \n",
1199  Ny,
1200  Cy.getX()*NM2BOHR,
1201  Cy.getY()*NM2BOHR,

1204  Nz,
1205  Cz.getX()*NM2BOHR,
1206  Cz.getY()*NM2BOHR,
1207  Cz.getZ()*NM2BOHR);
1208  for (pit = poles.begin(); pit < poles.end(); ++pit) {
1209 
1210  string elem = (*pit)->_name;
1211  int Z = 0;
1212  if (elem == "C") { Z = 6; }
1213  else if (elem == "H") { Z = 1; }
1214  else if (elem == "N") { Z = 7; }
1215  else if (elem == "O") { Z = 8; }
1216  else if (elem == "S") { Z = 16; }
1217 
1218  fprintf(out, "%5d %3.7f %3.7f %3.7f %3.7f \n",
1219  Z,
1220  0.000,

1222  (*pit)->getPos().getY() * NM2BOHR,
1223  (*pit)->getPos().getZ() * NM2BOHR);
1224  }
1225 
1226  int phiCount = 0;
1227  double int2V = 1/(4*M_PI*8.854187817e-12) * 1.602176487e-19 / 1.000e-9;
1228 
1229  for (int i = 0; i < Nx; ++i) {
1230  for (int j = 0; j < Ny; ++j) {
1231  for ( int k = 0; k < Nz; ++k) {
1232 
1233  Cxyz = C0 + i*Cx + j*Cy + k*Cz;
1234 
1235  double phi = 0.0;
1236  ++phiCount;
1237 
1238  for (pit = poles.begin(); pit < poles.end(); ++pit) {
1239  phi += actor.PotentialPerm(Cxyz, *(*pit));
1240  }
1241 
1242  fprintf(out, " %1.7E", phi * int2V);
1243  if ( (phiCount % 6) == 0 ) {
1244  fprintf(out, " \n");
1245  phiCount = 0;
1246  }
1247  }
1248  }
1249  }
1250 
1251  cout << " Calculated potential at " << Nx*Ny*Nz
1252  << " grid points. " << flush;
1253 
1254  // Calculate self-energy of configuration (just out of interest)
1255  double E = 0.0;
1256  vector< APolarSite* > ::iterator pit2;
1257  for (pit = poles.begin(); pit < poles.end(); ++pit) {
1258  for (pit2 = pit + 1; pit2 < poles.end(); ++pit2) {
1259  E += actor.EnergyInterESP(*(*pit), *(*pit2));
1260  }
1261  }
1262  double E2eV = 1.602176487e-19 * 1e9 * 1/(4*M_PI*8.854187817e-12);
1263  cout << endl << "... ... ... ... "
1264  << "Electrostatic self-energy of configuration: "
1265  << E*E2eV << " eV. ";

1488 void QMultipole::CalculateAlphaRigid(vector< APolarSite* > &poles,
1489  FILE *out, bool system) {
1490 
1491  vector< APolarSite* > ::iterator pit;
1492 
1493  double axx, axy, axz; // |
1494  double ayx, ayy, ayz; // |-> Polarizability tensor
1495  double azx, azy, azz; // |
1496 
1497  double siteU1x, siteU1y, siteU1z; // |-> Molecular ind. dipole
1498 
1499  double extFx, extFy, extFz; // |-> External applied field
1500 
1501  // +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
1502  // External field in x-direction //
1503  // +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
1504 
1505  siteU1x = siteU1y = siteU1z = 0.0;
1506 
1507  extFx = 0.1;
1508  extFy = 0.0;
1509  extFz = 0.0;
1510 
1511  // Set permanent field
1512  for (pit = poles.begin(); pit < poles.end(); ++pit) {
1513  (*pit)->FPx = extFx;
1514  (*pit)->FPy = extFy;
1515  (*pit)->FPz = extFz;
1516  }
1517 
1518  // Calculate induction field
1519  this->SiteAlphaInduce(NULL, poles);
1520 
1521  // Add up ind. dpl.s to yield molecular U1
1522  for (pit = poles.begin(); pit < poles.end(); ++pit) {
1523  siteU1x += (*pit)->U1x;
1524  siteU1y += (*pit)->U1y;
1525  siteU1z += (*pit)->U1z;
1526  }
1527 
1528  // Calculate associated column of polarizability tensor
1529  axx = - siteU1x / extFx;
1530  ayx = - siteU1y / extFx;
1531  azx = - siteU1z / extFx;
1532 
1533  // +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
1534  // External field in y-direction //
1535  // +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
1536 
1537  siteU1x = siteU1y = siteU1z = 0.0;
1538 
1539  extFx = 0.0;
1540  extFy = 0.1;
1541  extFz = 0.0;
1542 
1543  // Set permanent field
1544  for (pit = poles.begin(); pit < poles.end(); ++pit) {
1545  (*pit)->FPx = extFx;
1546  (*pit)->FPy = extFy;
1547  (*pit)->FPz = extFz;
1548  }
1549 
1550  // Calculate induction field
1551  this->SiteAlphaInduce(NULL, poles);
1552 
1553  // Add up ind. dpl.s to yield molecular U1
1554  for (pit = poles.begin(); pit < poles.end(); ++pit) {
1555  siteU1x += (*pit)->U1x;
1556  siteU1y += (*pit)->U1y;
1557  siteU1z += (*pit)->U1z;
1558  }
1559 
1560  // Calculate associated column of polarizability tensor
1561  axy = - siteU1x / extFy;
1562  ayy = - siteU1y / extFy;
1563  azy = - siteU1z / extFy;
1564 
1565  // +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
1566  // External field in z-direction //
1567  // +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
1568 
1569  siteU1x = siteU1y = siteU1z = 0.0;
1570 
1571  extFx = 0.0;
1572  extFy = 0.0;
1573  extFz = 0.1;
1574 
1575  // Set permanent field
1576  for (pit = poles.begin(); pit < poles.end(); ++pit) {
1577  (*pit)->FPx = extFx;
1578  (*pit)->FPy = extFy;
1579  (*pit)->FPz = extFz;
1580  }
1581 
1582  // Calculate induction field
1583  this->SiteAlphaInduce(NULL, poles);
1584 
1585  // Add up ind. dpl.s to yield molecular U1
1586  for (pit = poles.begin(); pit < poles.end(); ++pit) {
1587  siteU1x += (*pit)->U1x;
1588  siteU1y += (*pit)->U1y;
1589  siteU1z += (*pit)->U1z;
1590  }
1591 
1592  // Calculate associated column of polarizability tensor
1593  axz = - siteU1x / extFz;
1594  ayz = - siteU1y / extFz;
1595  azz = - siteU1z / extFz;
1596 
1597  // +++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
1598  // Sum, Trace, Diagonalization //
1599  // +++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
1600 
1601  // Sum over atomic polarizabilities
1602  double SUM_alpha = 0.0;
1603  for (pit = poles.begin(); pit < poles.end(); ++pit) {
1604  SUM_alpha += (*pit)->getIsoP();
1605  }
1606 
1607  double NM3_2_A3 = 1000.;
1608  SUM_alpha *= NM3_2_A3;
1609 
1610  // TODO Diagonalize polarizability tensor
1611  // For now, trace is enough
1612  double ISO_alpha = (axx + ayy + azz) / 3.;
1613 
1614  ISO_alpha *= NM3_2_A3;
1615 
1616  // Eigenvalues of polarizability tensor
1617  matrix alpha = matrix( vec(axx,ayx,azx),
1618  vec(axy,ayy,azy),
1619  vec(axz,ayz,azz) );
1620  matrix::eigensystem_t EIGEN;
1621  alpha.SolveEigensystem(EIGEN);
1622 
1623 
1624  if (! system) {
1625  cout << endl << "... ... ... ... Sum over atomic alphas: "
1626  << SUM_alpha << " A**3.";
1627  cout << endl << "... ... ... ... 1/3 trace of alpha tensor: "
1628  << ISO_alpha << " A**3.";
1629  cout << endl << "... ... ... ... Eigenvalues: "
1630  << EIGEN.eigenvalues[0]*NM3_2_A3 << " A**3, "
1631  << EIGEN.eigenvalues[1]*NM3_2_A3 << " A**3, "
1632  << EIGEN.eigenvalues[2]*NM3_2_A3 << " A**3. ";
1633  }
1634 
1635  if (_alphaOutFile != "noname" && _alphaOutFile != "") {
1636 
1637  vec x = EIGEN.eigenvecs[0];
1638  vec y = EIGEN.eigenvecs[1];
1639  vec z = EIGEN.eigenvecs[2];
1640 
1641  if (! system) {
1642  fprintf(out, "Polarizability tensor in global frame \n");
1643  fprintf(out, "%4.7f %4.7f %4.7f \n", axx*NM3_2_A3, axy*NM3_2_A3, axz*NM3_2_A3);
1644  fprintf(out, "%4.7f %4.7f %4.7f \n", ayx*NM3_2_A3, ayy*NM3_2_A3, ayz*NM3_2_A3);
1645  fprintf(out, "%4.7f %4.7f %4.7f \n", azx*NM3_2_A3, azy*NM3_2_A3, azz*NM3_2_A3);
1646  fprintf(out, "\n");
1647  fprintf(out, "Polarizability tensor in eigenframe \n");
1648  fprintf(out, "%4.7f %4.7f %4.7f \n", EIGEN.eigenvalues[0]*NM3_2_A3,0.,0.);
1649  fprintf(out, "%4.7f %4.7f %4.7f \n", 0.,EIGEN.eigenvalues[1]*NM3_2_A3,0.);
1650  fprintf(out, "%4.7f %4.7f %4.7f \n", 0.,0.,EIGEN.eigenvalues[2]*NM3_2_A3);
1651  fprintf(out, "\n");
1652  fprintf(out, "Polarizability tensor main axes \n");
1653  fprintf(out, "%4.7f %4.7f %4.7f \n", x.getX(),x.getY(),x.getZ());
1654  fprintf(out, "%4.7f %4.7f %4.7f \n", y.getX(),y.getY(),y.getZ());
1655  fprintf(out, "%4.7f %4.7f %4.7f \n", z.getX(),z.getY(),z.getZ());

1657  else {

1661  EIGEN.eigenvalues[1]*NM3_2_A3,
1662  EIGEN.eigenvalues[2]*NM3_2_A3);

1672 void QMultipole::SiteAlphaInduce(Topology *top, vector<APolarSite*> &poles) {
1673 
1674  int maxIter = this->_maxIter;
1675  double wSOR = this->_wSOR_N;
1676  double eTOL = this->_epsTol;
1677 
1678  vector< APolarSite* >::iterator pit1;
1679  vector< APolarSite* >::iterator pit2;
1680 
1681  Interactor actor = Interactor(top, this);
1682 
1683  // Induce to first order
1684  for (pit1 = poles.begin(); pit1 < poles.end(); ++pit1) {
1685  (*pit1)->InduceDirect();
1686  }
1687 
1688 
1689  int iter = 0;
1690  for ( ; iter < maxIter; ++iter) {
1691 
1692  // Reset induction field
1693  for (pit1 = poles.begin(); pit1 < poles.end(); ++pit1) {
1694  (*pit1)->ResetFieldU();
1695  }
1696 
1697  // Calculate higher-order induction field
1698  for (pit1 = poles.begin(); pit1 < poles.end(); ++pit1) {
1699  for (pit2 = pit1 + 1; pit2 < poles.end(); ++pit2) {
1700  actor.FieldInduAlpha(*(*pit1),*(*pit2));
1701  }
1702  }
1703 
1704  // Induce dipoles
1705  for (pit1 = poles.begin(); pit1 < poles.end(); ++pit1) {
1706  (*pit1)->Induce(wSOR);
1707  }
1708 
1709  // Check for convergence
1710  bool converged = true;
1711  double maxdU = -1;
1712  double avgdU = 0.0;
1713  int baseN = 0;
1714 
1715  for (pit1 = poles.begin(); pit1 < poles.end(); ++pit1) {
1716  double dU = (*pit1)->HistdU();
1717  avgdU += dU;
1718  ++baseN;
1719  if ( dU > maxdU ) { maxdU = dU; }
1720  if ( dU > eTOL ) { converged = false; }
1721  }
1722 
1723  avgdU /= baseN;
1724  if (avgdU < eTOL/10.) { converged = true; }
1725 
1726  //cout << endl << "ITER" << iter << " | MAX dU " << maxdU
1727  // << " | AVG dU " << avgdU;
1728 
1729  // Break if converged
1730  if (converged) { break; }
1731  else if (iter == maxIter - 1) {
1732  cout << endl << "... ... ... "
1733  << "WARNING Induced multipoles did not converge to precision: "
1734  << " AVG dU:U " << avgdU << flush;
1735  break;
1736  }
1737  }
1738 }

2486 int QMultipole::SiteOpQMultipole::Induce(int state) {
2487 
2488  double wSOR = (state == 0) ? _master->_wSOR_N : _master->_wSOR_C;
2489  double eTOL = this->_master->_epsTol;
2490  int maxI = this->_master->_maxIter;
2491 
2492  vector< vector<APolarSite*> > ::iterator sit1;

2494  vector< APolarSite* > ::iterator pit1;
2495  vector< APolarSite* > ::iterator pit2;

2498  // Inter-site fields (arising from perm. m'poles) //
2499  // ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
2500 
2501 // cout << endl << "... ... ... 0th-order field" << flush;
2502  for (sit1 = _polsPolSphere.begin();
2503  sit1 < _polsPolSphere.end();
2504  ++sit1) {

2506  sit2 < _polsPolSphere.end();
2507  ++sit2) {
2508

2510  for (pit2 = (*sit2).begin(); pit2 < (*sit2).end(); ++pit2) {
2511 
2512  _actor.FieldPerm(*(*pit1), *(*pit2));
2513  }}
2514  }}
2515 
2516  // +++++++++++++++++++ //
2517  // 1st-order induction //
2518  // +++++++++++++++++++ //
2519 
2520 // cout << " | Induce " << endl;
2521  if (state == 0) { // OVERRIDE
2522  for (sit1 = _polsPolSphere.begin();
2523  sit1 < _polsPolSphere.end();
2524  ++sit1) {
2525 
2526  for (pit1 = (*sit1).begin(); pit1 < (*sit1).end(); ++pit1) {
2527  (*pit1)->InduceDirect();
2528  }
2529  }
2530  }
2531 
2532 
2533 
2534  // ++++++++++++++++++++++ //
2535  // Higher-order induction //
2536  // ++++++++++++++++++++++ //
2537 
2538  int iter = 0;
2539 // boost::progress_timer T;
2540  for ( ; iter < maxI; ++iter) {
2541 
2542  // Reset fields FUx, FUy, FUz
2543 // cout << "\r... ... ... Reset (" << iter << ")" << flush;
2544  for (sit1 = _polsPolSphere.begin();
2545  sit1 < _polsPolSphere.end();
2546  ++sit1) {
2547 
2548  for (pit1 = (*sit1).begin(); pit1 < (*sit1).end(); ++pit1) {
2549  (*pit1)->ResetFieldU();
2550  }
2551  }
2552 
2553  // Intra-site contribution to induction field
2554 // cout << " | Intra-Site (" << iter << ")" << flush;
2555  for (sit1 = _polsPolSphere.begin();
2556  sit1 < _polsPolSphere.end();
2557  ++sit1) {
2558 
2559  for (pit1 = (*sit1).begin(); pit1 < (*sit1).end(); ++pit1) {
2560  for (pit2 = pit1 + 1; pit2 < (*sit1).end(); ++pit2) {
2561 
2562  _actor.FieldIndu(*(*pit1),*(*pit2));
2563  }}
2564  }
2565 
2566  // Inter-site contribution to induction field
2567 // cout << " | Inter-Site (" << iter << ")" << flush;
2568  //boost::progress_display show_progress( _polsPolSphere.size() );
2569 // T.restart();
2570  for (sit1 = _polsPolSphere.begin();
2571  sit1 < _polsPolSphere.end();
2572  ++sit1) {
2573  for (sit2 = sit1 + 1;
2574  sit2 < _polsPolSphere.end();
2575  ++sit2) {
2576 
2577  for (pit1 = (*sit1).begin(); pit1 < (*sit1).end(); ++pit1) {
2578  for (pit2 = (*sit2).begin(); pit2 < (*sit2).end(); ++pit2) {
2579 
2580  _actor.FieldIndu(*(*pit1), *(*pit2));
2581  }}
2582  }}
2583 // cout << " | dt " << T.elapsed() << flush;
2584 
2585  // Induce again
2586 // cout << " | Induce (" << iter << ")" << flush;
2587  for (sit1 = _polsPolSphere.begin();
2588  sit1 < _polsPolSphere.end();
2589  ++sit1) {
2590 
2591  for (pit1 = (*sit1).begin(); pit1 < (*sit1).end(); ++pit1) {
2592  (*pit1)->Induce(wSOR);
2593  }
2594  }
2595 
2596  // Check for convergence
2597 // cout << " | Check (" << iter << ")" << flush;
2598  bool converged = true;
2599  double maxdU = -1;
2600  double avgdU = 0.0;
2601  int baseN = 0;
2602  for (sit1 = _polsPolSphere.begin();
2603  sit1 < _polsPolSphere.end();
2604  ++sit1) {
2605 
2606  for (pit1 = (*sit1).begin(); pit1 < (*sit1).end(); ++pit1) {
2607  double dU = (*pit1)->HistdU();
2608  avgdU += dU;
2609  ++baseN;
2610  if ( dU > maxdU ) { maxdU = dU; }
2611  if ( dU > eTOL ) { converged = false; }
2612  }
2613  }
2614  avgdU /= baseN;
2615  if (avgdU < eTOL/10.) { converged = true; }
2616 
2617 // cout << " | MAX dU " << maxdU
2618 // << " | AVG dU " << avgdU
2619 // << " | SOR " << wSOR << flush;
2620 
2621  // Break if converged
2622  if (converged) {
2623  break;
2624  }
2625  else if (iter == maxI - 1) {
2626  this->_master->LockCout();
2627  cout << endl << "... ... ... WARNING Induced multipoles for site "
2628  << _seg->getId() << " - state " << state
2629  << " did not converge to precision: "
2630  << " AVG dU:U " << avgdU << flush;
2631  this->_master->UnlockCout();
2632  break;
2633  }
2634  }
2635 
2636  return iter;
2637

2640 // << " - Iterations " << iter << flush;

2813 inline double QMultipole::Interactor::PotentialPerm(vec r,
2814  APolarSite &pol) {
2815 
2816  // NOTE >>> e12 points from polar site 1 to polar site 2 <<< NOTE //
2817  e12 = pol.getPos() - r;
2818  R = 1/abs(e12);
2819  R2 = R*R;
2820  R3 = R2*R;
2821  R4 = R3*R;
2822  R5 = R4*R;
2823  e12 *= R;
2824 
2825 
2826 
2827 
2828  rbx = - pol._locX * e12;
2829  rby = - pol._locY * e12;
2830  rbz = - pol._locZ * e12;
2831 
2832  double phi00 = 0.0;
2833 
2834  phi00 += T00_00() * pol.Q00;
2835 
2836  if (pol._rank > 0) {
2837  phi00 += T00_1x() * pol.Q1x;
2838  phi00 += T00_1y() * pol.Q1y;
2839  phi00 += T00_1z() * pol.Q1z;
2840  }
2841 
2842  if (pol._rank > 1) {
2843  phi00 += T00_20() * pol.Q20;
2844  phi00 += T00_21c() * pol.Q21c;
2845  phi00 += T00_21s() * pol.Q21s;
2846  phi00 += T00_22c() * pol.Q22c;
2847  phi00 += T00_22s() * pol.Q22s;
2848  }
2849 
2850  return phi00;
2851 }
2852 
2856 inline vec QMultipole::Interactor::FieldPermESF(vec r,
2857  APolarSite &pol) {
2858  // NOTE >>> e12 points from polar site 1 to polar site 2 <<< NOTE //
2859  e12 = pol.getPos() - r;
2860  R = 1/abs(e12);
2861  R2 = R*R;
2862  R3 = R2*R;
2863  R4 = R3*R;
2864  R5 = R4*R;
2865  e12 *= R;
2866 
2867  rax = e12.getX();
2868  ray = e12.getY();
